26:20.835 --> 26:22.877
Come on. You can't
leave me hanging on that.

26:22.961 --> 26:27.419
"See you at Scrabble practice, kid"?
What's that?

26:27.502 --> 26:29.919
I'm a member of
the BayArea Scrabble Club.

26:29.961 --> 26:32.502
- Pathetic, I know.
- Wow.

26:32.585 --> 26:34.961
- What?
- That is pathetic.

26:35.003 --> 26:37.421
Shut up.

26:37.462 --> 26:40.212
At least I can spell.
What can you do?

26:40.296 --> 26:42.962
- I throw a mean yo-yo.
- You know what?

26:43.004 --> 26:46.546
- No more caramel corn for you.
- I'm serious.

26:46.628 --> 26:49.962
How'd you get into it? I've never met
a member of a Scrabble Club before.

26:50.045 --> 26:51.963
That's for sure.

26:53.879 --> 26:56.879
When my parents came over
from Italy...

26:56.921 --> 26:59.963
the yjoined a Scrabble Club
so they could learn English.

27:01.046 --> 27:05.463
After my mom died, my dad became,
like, obsessed with the game...

27:05.547 --> 27:08.089
and wanted me to play with him
all the time...

27:08.172 --> 27:10.797
so I guess, in a way,
I was destined.

27:12.131 --> 27:14.047
C-O-O-L.

27:22.340 --> 27:23.840
What are you doing?

27:27.340 --> 27:29.340
I only eat the brown ones.

27:29.424 --> 27:30.841
Because?

27:32.132 --> 27:34.923
'Cause I figure they have
less artificial coloring...

27:34.965 --> 27:38.258
'cause chocolate's already brown.

27:38.341 --> 27:40.550
That's very scientific of you,
dr. Steve.

27:40.633 --> 27:41.800
Thank you.

27:45.592 --> 27:47.717
So where would one go
to see a Scrabble match?

27:47.800 --> 27:50.550
Oh, look. It's starting.

27:56.593 --> 28:01.384
Andcloser

28:01.426 --> 28:05.010
tome

28:10.468 --> 28:12.969
- Oh, that'sbeautiful.
- Youlikeit?

28:13.052 --> 28:14.510
Yes.

28:28.887 --> 28:33.179
This is by far the coolest thing
I've ever done in this city.

28:37.305 --> 28:41.598
the closer youare

28:41.639 --> 28:46.098
- The brigh ter the starsglow
- Wanna dance?

28:46.140 --> 28:50.891
I don't know. I haven't danced
in quite some time.

28:50.974 --> 28:54.433
- Okay.
- Girl asks you to dance, you dance.

28:56.849 --> 29:00.433
Burt's right.
Yes, Mary, I would love to dance.

29:01.891 --> 29:05.099
- No pressure.
- It's too late now.

29:13.267 --> 29:14.683
Okay.

29:23.018 --> 29:25.976
Where'd you learn
to dance like this?

29:26.018 --> 29:28.143
Ballroom class.

29:28.185 --> 29:30.477
Oh, you're gay.

29:30.518 --> 29:32.809
Oh, yeah, the gayest.

29:38.352 --> 29:41.852
My mother put me
in ballroom classes...

29:41.935 --> 29:43.894
when I was eight years old.

29:43.935 --> 29:47.478
She wanted me to be Fred Astaire.
I wanted to be Marcus Welby.

29:49.102 --> 29:51.812
So now you're
a little bit ofboth?

29:53.978 --> 29:56.103
I think you're being kind.

29:56.145 --> 29:58.978
You can stop that.
I'm gonna blush.

30:03.520 --> 30:05.438
How's your thumb?

30:06.855 --> 30:08.271
Never better.

30:29.814 --> 30:31.689
YMCA.

30:31.773 --> 30:34.481
My next Scrabble match
is Saturday...

30:34.522 --> 30:37.565
at 1:00 at the north side YMCA.

30:37.648 --> 30:40.149
It'll be the social event
of the season.

30:41.607 --> 30:43.857
Maybe you should be there.

30:47.982 --> 30:51.233
- Maybe you shouldn't step on my foot.
- Did I?

30:51.275 --> 30:52.816
- Yes.
- I'm sorry.

30:52.900 --> 30:55.025
That's okay.
Just don't let it happen again.

30:56.900 --> 30:58.357
don't tell me what to do.

30:58.441 --> 30:59.858
don't what?

31:36.487 --> 31:38.111
Holy shit!

31:38.195 --> 31:40.612
Are you guys crazy?
This isn't funny!

31:40.694 --> 31:44.278
I am thinking teal for the bridesmaids.
What do you think?

31:46.612 --> 31:48.945
Good morning. Earth to Mary.

31:49.029 --> 31:51.529
What is up with you?
You're different.

31:51.613 --> 31:54.112
I'm not different.
How am I different?

31:54.196 --> 31:56.196
You can't stop smiling.

31:57.613 --> 31:59.613
I'm not smiling.
Am I smiling?

31:59.696 --> 32:01.945
Like a fool.

32:02.029 --> 32:04.364
- Tell me.
- It's nothing.

32:04.447 --> 32:06.946
Then stop smiling.

32:07.030 --> 32:09.739
- I can't.
- Okay, who is he?

32:14.905 --> 32:16.864
Okay. No, no!

32:16.946 --> 32:20.239
Mr. Kotsioupolis, you cannot throw
plates at the Ritz-fucking-Carlton!

32:21.323 --> 32:22.490
It's okay.

32:22.573 --> 32:24.323
This is like a fairy tale.

32:24.406 --> 32:26.907
He saves your life.
You dance under the stars.

32:26.989 --> 32:29.698
- You kiss in the rain.
- Almost kissed.

32:29.782 --> 32:33.866
I don't know, Fran. I've been so out
of the dating-relationship loop.

32:33.949 --> 32:35.282
You?

32:35.324 --> 32:39.532
You know, those who can't do, teach?
Those who can't wed, plan.

32:39.616 --> 32:42.532
With my help, you could marry
this man in three months.

32:43.407 --> 32:46.658
I have totally lost control.
Will you please, please, please help me?

32:46.741 --> 32:48.617
Penny, if you can't beat 'em...

32:49.742 --> 32:52.450
- What has gotten into you?
- She met a guy.

32:52.533 --> 32:55.367
You met a guy? You mean...

33:00.659 --> 33:03.868
- I wanna hear all about it!
- I owe you one, Penny.

33:03.952 --> 33:06.035
You do. You owe me one!

33:08.284 --> 33:11.202
- Hello, Rene. How are you?
- Great.

33:11.285 --> 33:13.701
Listen, they're gonna be
signing up for six classes.

33:13.785 --> 33:16.451
Sojust be sure
to pay up front, okay?

33:16.493 --> 33:18.702
Basil himself
is gonna be here today.

33:18.786 --> 33:20.702
- Really?
- Yes.

33:22.702 --> 33:25.203
I'll have to call you back.
Okay. Bye.

33:26.619 --> 33:28.869
Mary, what are you doing here?

33:28.953 --> 33:31.328
Oh, my God.
I'm so embarrassed.

33:31.411 --> 33:33.329
I may be a hell
of a businesswoman...

33:33.412 --> 33:36.371
but when I dance,
I look like a retarded string bean.

33:36.454 --> 33:38.454
I thought your class
wasn't till Thursday though.

33:38.536 --> 33:41.246
I know. We had to change it.
But this is perfect.

33:41.287 --> 33:44.662
You can finally meet Eddie.
Come here. Eddie.

33:44.745 --> 33:46.662
Eddie, come here.

33:46.745 --> 33:48.788
I want you to meet
the wedding planner.

33:48.829 --> 33:51.538
The two most important people
in my life set eyes on one another.

33:51.621 --> 33:54.040
Eddie, this is Mary,
the wedding planner.

33:54.831 --> 33:56.748
Mary, this is my fiance Eddie.

34:09.873 --> 34:13.583
- Mary, are you okay?
- Uh-huh. Yup. Good.

34:16.208 --> 34:17.917
Let's see who that is.

34:20.583 --> 34:22.583
Hi, dad. Wait.

34:22.668 --> 34:25.458
I can't hear you. Hang on.
All right. Okay, I got you.

34:26.875 --> 34:29.208
Okay, I'm losing you again.
I'm sorry.

34:29.251 --> 34:32.585
Shoot. Okay, wait, wait.
Hello. Do you hear me?

34:32.668 --> 34:32.835
Quickly, people.
Get your tootsies out here, pronto.

34:32.835 --> 34:35.793
Quickly, people.
Get your tootsies out here, pronto.

34:35.877 --> 34:38.877
Welcome to the Basil St. Mosely
School of dance.

34:38.918 --> 34:41.377
I am Basil St. Mosely.

34:41.418 --> 34:44.126
Hang on. I can't hear you.
Wait a second. I can't hear you.

34:44.210 --> 34:46.418
You're breaking up. Hang on.

34:46.460 --> 34:47.920
There you go.

34:47.962 --> 34:51.628
I'd like all my lovely couples,
dancing partners, paired up in twos...

34:51.670 --> 34:53.837
ready to dance, not next week,
not tomorrow, but now.

34:53.920 --> 34:55.837
- Dance with Eddie.
- I can't.

34:55.920 --> 34:58.169
Quickly.
Is there a problem in the room?

34:58.211 --> 35:01.336
Pronto, people. I'd like us to still
be young when this class is over.

35:01.378 --> 35:03.004
I have to take this call.

35:03.046 --> 35:05.337
darling, I understand you're busy.
I'm busy too.

35:05.379 --> 35:07.546
- You're holding up the class.
- She's with him.

35:07.629 --> 35:08.879
All right.

35:08.963 --> 35:12.129
Mary, watch out for his thumb.
He hurt it saving some old lady.

35:12.212 --> 35:14.754
- Sorry, I can't.
- Listen, I got a prior engagement.

35:14.838 --> 35:16.796
Interesting choice of words.

35:16.839 --> 35:19.089
Wallfowers,
it's time to blossom and bloom.

35:19.172 --> 35:22.839
Obviously, what we have here, people,
is a fear ofdancing.

35:22.922 --> 35:26.630
It's my firm belief
we must conquer one's fears.

35:26.713 --> 35:29.922
Now, I have to gauge
what I am dealing with...

35:30.005 --> 35:32.673
so I will play music,
you will dance...

35:32.714 --> 35:34.464
and I will observe.

35:34.548 --> 35:35.631
Okay, Rene?

35:35.714 --> 35:35.881
