35:45.257 --> 35:46.674
Yes.

35:49.007 --> 35:51.590
- Old lady, huh?
- Listen, this is...

35:51.674 --> 35:53.966
- You told me your name was Steve.
- It is Steve.

35:54.007 --> 35:56.590
My last name is Edison.
Fran calls me Eddie. It's a nickname.

35:56.674 --> 36:00.049
I have a better nickname for you.
How about common, cheating, sleazy...

36:00.133 --> 36:01.216
If you're thinking...

36:01.299 --> 36:04.008
What I'm thinking involves
a machete and a pair ofpliers.

36:04.050 --> 36:05.134
Okay.

36:09.551 --> 36:12.134
- The day that you had the accident.
- That was a special day.

36:12.217 --> 36:13.509
It was. I was running late.

36:13.592 --> 36:15.217
How convenient.

36:15.300 --> 36:18.634
I was meeting Fran and our wedding
planner, which you turned out to be.

36:18.717 --> 36:20.593
What are the odds?

36:20.635 --> 36:22.801
dance. Dance!

36:25.051 --> 36:28.801
don't dance around the issue. You didn't
show 'cause you don't wanna get married.

36:28.884 --> 36:31.844
- I see it all the time.
- You see what?

36:31.927 --> 36:34.969
Why'd you tell your fiancee
you saved an old lady?

36:35.052 --> 36:36.927
Exactly!

36:37.010 --> 36:39.844
You think you want to get married,
but you don't.

36:39.885 --> 36:43.344
You're pitiful and confused, looking
to get some hot pepper wherever you can.

36:43.386 --> 36:46.011
Mary, you have no idea
what you're talking about.

36:46.053 --> 36:47.262
Yeah?

36:47.345 --> 36:48.928
Why did you go
to the movies with me?

36:49.011 --> 36:51.679
Why did Steve go to the movies
with you? Let's see.

36:51.762 --> 36:54.095
First of all,
Steve likes the movies.

36:54.178 --> 36:55.762
Steve had the night off.

36:55.846 --> 36:57.928
Steve said, "Hey, you know what?

36:58.011 --> 37:00.971
A movie sounds good."
Plus he got an invitation.

37:01.012 --> 37:03.221
Why is Steve referring to himself
in the third person?

37:03.304 --> 37:05.221
What are you talking about?

37:05.304 --> 37:08.972
Think you can double-talk your way out,
throw me off your scent? I smell you!

37:09.012 --> 37:11.680
And I smell like sweet red plums
and grilled cheese sandwiches.

37:11.763 --> 37:13.179
- What?
- Yes.

37:13.221 --> 37:15.764
- So you said before you passed out.
- I did not!

37:15.848 --> 37:18.806
You did too. If anybody was
looking to get some, it's M-A-R-Y.

37:18.889 --> 37:20.514
You are hideous.

37:20.597 --> 37:22.973
Okay. Then why'd you
ask me to dance?

37:23.056 --> 37:24.556
- I didn't.
- You did too.

37:24.597 --> 37:26.931
- I did not.
- You said, "Would you like to dance?"

37:27.014 --> 37:30.807
And even if I did,
I'm not the one who's engaged.

37:30.890 --> 37:32.807
It was a dance.

37:32.890 --> 37:34.974
Whoop-dee-doo.
It didn't mean anything.

37:36.141 --> 37:37.765
Then why'd you almost kiss me?

37:40.515 --> 37:43.265
This pair, this lovely couple...

37:43.348 --> 37:46.017
they have it,
they know what it takes.

37:47.558 --> 37:49.683
Very well done.

37:51.142 --> 37:52.349
We need to powwow.

37:55.683 --> 37:58.225
As soon as dad mentioned it,
I went, "Of course."

37:58.308 --> 38:01.268
Everybody knows that
it's the place to get married.

38:01.309 --> 38:04.018
Sure, Fran.
A vineyard sounds perfect.

38:04.101 --> 38:06.351
- We should check it out right away.
- I already have.

38:06.434 --> 38:10.600
We have reservations for this weekend,
but you'll have to take off Friday.

38:10.684 --> 38:14.517
Friday? Friday's not good for me.
I have a diverticulitis seminar planned.

38:14.600 --> 38:17.852
- Okay. Saturday.
- Saturday.

38:17.935 --> 38:20.893
Saturday. All right, Mary?
Thanks for everything.

38:20.935 --> 38:23.394
Nice to meet you. Thanks for the dance.
We'll let you know how it all goes.

38:23.436 --> 38:26.727
- Pleasure to meet you.
- Wait a second. She's coming with us.

38:26.768 --> 38:28.352
- I'm coming?
- She's comin'?

38:28.436 --> 38:29.394
Yes.

38:29.477 --> 38:31.520
You are not quitting
the donolly wedding!

38:32.936 --> 38:35.312
I gotta tell Geri
I'm off the account.

38:36.395 --> 38:37.562
Hold on.

38:37.644 --> 38:39.270
Listen...

38:39.353 --> 38:43.811
the only good reason to quit a wedding
is if you break the cardinal rule...

38:43.853 --> 38:47.438
which is ridiculous because we both know
you did not fall in love with the groom.

38:48.604 --> 38:49.563
What?

38:51.688 --> 38:53.229
You didn't.

38:54.937 --> 38:56.688
Bad.

38:56.770 --> 38:58.730
No, of course not.

38:59.896 --> 39:02.896
I'd never get emotionally involved.

39:02.980 --> 39:05.105
Never. Never.

39:06.274 --> 39:07.566
It's the doctor.

39:09.232 --> 39:12.190
I'm confused. Is it the doctor,
or did you fall for the groom?

39:12.274 --> 39:16.108
No, the doctor is the groom.
The groom is the doctor.

39:16.150 --> 39:18.650
The doctor is Fran donolly's fiance!

39:18.692 --> 39:21.108
The dumpster girl
is your wedding planner?

39:21.191 --> 39:23.108
Yes. I'm in hell.

39:23.191 --> 39:25.275
And I'm in heaven.
Now you can fix me up with her.

39:25.358 --> 39:28.609
I'm not fixing you up, dr. John.
Look, this is complicated enough.

39:28.692 --> 39:31.693
You are one of the top
wedding planners...

39:31.735 --> 39:35.693
in this great, big,
thriving metropolis.

39:35.776 --> 39:38.735
Look on the positive side.
He got you to open up again.

39:38.818 --> 39:40.776
Thank the bastard and move on.

39:40.818 --> 39:43.943
You cannot tell me you would sacrifice
your entire career over this!

39:43.985 --> 39:47.569
You're not telling me that you think
it's a mistake to marry Fran now?

39:47.652 --> 39:50.485
