I'm sorry about Napa.

59:41.831 --> 59:45.123
I didn't mean to call you
bitter and cynical. You're not.

59:45.206 --> 59:49.458
And I'm sorry, what I said about
your marriage being doomed to fail.

59:51.416 --> 59:54.332
Well, I apologize for saying
you were just an opportunity.

59:55.624 --> 59:57.585
That was pretty ugly of me.

59:57.626 --> 01:00:01.626
And I was only half serious
about the teal bridesmaid thing.

01:00:02.835 --> 01:00:05.752
Well, at least I have
a 50-50 chance, right?

01:00:07.377 --> 01:00:10.335
You and Fran are gonna be
real happy together.

01:00:11.461 --> 01:00:14.377
So are you and Massimo.
It's gonna work.

01:00:14.461 --> 01:00:18.295
Yeah, well, um,
we're not engaged anymore.

01:00:19.795 --> 01:00:22.086
- Really?
- Really.

01:00:23.545 --> 01:00:25.503
- Are you okay with that?
- Yeah.

01:00:27.378 --> 01:00:30.295
It was more my dad
trying to get us together.

01:00:31.962 --> 01:00:34.171
Why would he want to do that?

01:00:38.379 --> 01:00:41.337
Well, probably because
he was so happy with my mom.

01:00:56.756 --> 01:01:00.089
Fran said to go forward
with the violet chocolate...

01:01:00.173 --> 01:01:02.840
- The chocolate one?
- The one that you suggested.

01:01:02.923 --> 01:01:05.215
Good. Then I'll
put in that order today.

01:01:05.298 --> 01:01:07.506
- How is Fran?
- She's good.

01:01:07.590 --> 01:01:11.339
She's making deals, kickin' butt.
You know, being Fran.

01:01:15.339 --> 01:01:17.507
Oh, nicely done.

01:01:20.924 --> 01:01:23.382
- Thank you, Mary.
- You're welcome.

01:01:23.424 --> 01:01:25.050
You wanna keep it?

01:01:26.258 --> 01:01:27.716
Sure.

01:01:33.633 --> 01:01:36.092
Wow, it's a nice day.

01:01:37.301 --> 01:01:40.259
I agree with you
about the small wedding.

01:01:41.633 --> 01:01:44.051
That's the way I'd do it too.

01:01:52.885 --> 01:01:54.344
Papa.

01:02:00.427 --> 01:02:03.261
How nice to see you.

01:02:04.345 --> 01:02:05.595
Where's my father?

01:02:05.677 --> 01:02:09.553
He's out buying the balloons
for Burt's birthday party.

01:02:10.303 --> 01:02:11.927
Tell him I was here.

01:02:11.969 --> 01:02:13.595
Wait, Mary.

01:02:14.345 --> 01:02:15.678
Are you mad with me?

01:02:15.761 --> 01:02:17.304
Yes...

01:02:17.346 --> 01:02:19.095
I'm mad at you.

01:02:19.179 --> 01:02:21.554
You told my father
we were engaged.

01:02:21.637 --> 01:02:24.554
He tried to measure me
for a wedding dress.

01:02:24.637 --> 01:02:27.596
What is the matter with you?
You never listen.

01:02:27.679 --> 01:02:31.347
Massimo, we are not going to
be together like that. Okay?

01:02:31.430 --> 01:02:34.929
- And why are you in my father's house?
- I am sorry. I will leave you alone.

01:02:36.013 --> 01:02:39.971
From now on, I'll no longer bother you.
We will be just friends.

01:02:40.013 --> 01:02:42.971
Oh, you thinkwe can be friends
just like that?

01:02:43.013 --> 01:02:46.389
I want to apologize
for any madness I caused you.

01:02:46.473 --> 01:02:47.806
Is this a trick?

01:02:47.848 --> 01:02:49.806
No tricks.
I'm very serious.

01:02:50.848 --> 01:02:53.389
I just want for us to be
buddy-buddy.

01:02:54.848 --> 01:02:57.306
I promise you.

01:02:59.181 --> 01:03:01.599
do you have plans for dinner?

01:03:01.682 --> 01:03:05.474
As a friend, I want to
make for you a wonderful...

01:03:05.557 --> 01:03:07.474
American dish.

01:03:08.641 --> 01:03:10.307
Sit. I will start.

01:03:12.724 --> 01:03:15.265
That's your specialty?
Instant macaroni and cheese?

01:03:15.307 --> 01:03:17.725
It is a low-budget wonder.

01:03:17.808 --> 01:03:20.224
Already today,
I've eaten three boxes.

01:03:21.433 --> 01:03:24.017
Nothing like
a well-balanced diet.

01:03:37.310 --> 01:03:41.060
- You remind me so much of your mother.
- You don't remember my mother.

01:03:41.143 --> 01:03:43.185
Yeah, I remember your mother.

01:03:44.268 --> 01:03:46.435
She had the same big smile...

01:03:46.477 --> 01:03:48.644
and the same dark hair.

01:03:48.727 --> 01:03:52.644
She had no nail on her little finger.
I don't remember why.

01:03:54.685 --> 01:03:58.228
A brick fell on it when she was little.
It never grew back.

01:03:58.311 --> 01:04:00.479
You see?
We have much history together.

01:04:00.519 --> 01:04:02.479
I guess we sort ofdo.

01:04:08.561 --> 01:04:11.479
You look like
you have much on your mind.

01:04:11.562 --> 01:04:12.978
Not at all.

01:04:14.103 --> 01:04:15.729
Well, we're friends...

01:04:15.771 --> 01:04:19.188
and friends listen when friends
are not feeling so good...

01:04:19.271 --> 01:04:21.355
so please to tell me.

01:04:25.063 --> 01:04:27.063
There's nothing to tell.

01:04:27.146 --> 01:04:30.064
I thought I could control everything,
and I can't.

01:04:31.189 --> 01:04:34.147
I met someone who I thought was...

01:04:34.189 --> 01:04:35.689
Well, he's not.

01:04:40.897 --> 01:04:44.064
did you ever like somebody,
but the timing was off?

01:04:45.273 --> 01:04:46.524
Way off?

01:04:47.940 --> 01:04:51.357
You feel things
you should not be feeling?

01:04:54.273 --> 01:04:56.190
I'm not making any sense.

01:04:58.273 --> 01:05:00.233
You make much sense.

01:05:02.608 --> 01:05:05.982
You long for him
the way I long for you.

01:05:09.693 --> 01:05:11.610
I don't want you to think...

01:05:11.693 --> 01:05:13.610
I want to tell you something.

01:05:15.528 --> 01:05:18.110
You need to learn patience.

01:05:19.277 --> 01:05:21.236
Love can't always be perfect.

01:05:21.277 --> 01:05:23.236
Love is just love.

01:05:28.528 --> 01:05:30.487
My mom used to say that.

01:05:30.529 --> 01:05:33.112
Your mother was a very wise woman.

01:05:36.487 --> 01:05:37.821
Eat.

01:05:49.239 --> 01:05:54.363
We'll start with camellias as a base,
and anything else that jumps out at you.

01:05:55.446 --> 01:05:57.863
- Let me know.
- Okay.

01:05:57.947 --> 01:05:59.697
Roses.

01:05:59.781 --> 01:06:01.198
Wreaths.

01:06:01.281 --> 01:06:03.365
We don't need any more statues.

01:06:04.531 --> 01:06:05.823
How about this beauty?

01:06:05.864 --> 01:06:07.989
Interesting.

01:06:08.031 --> 01:06:10.614
This is called a bleeding heart...

01:06:10.697 --> 01:06:13.489
the official funeral fower
of Tibet.

01:06:13.531 --> 01:06:15.740
I knew I'd be good at this.

01:06:16.865 --> 01:06:18.782
I'll take
some Slit-My-Wrists-Susans...

01:06:18.865 --> 01:06:20.782
and we'll be ready.

01:06:24.282 --> 01:06:26.199
How'd you guys meet?

01:06:26.282 --> 01:06:28.366
- Me and Fran?
- Yeah.

01:06:28.449 --> 01:06:29.908
College.

01:06:29.991 --> 01:06:31.950
She was in one of your classes?

01:06:31.991 --> 01:06:34.117
No, she was a bookie, actually.

01:06:34.200 --> 01:06:36.658
- Fran was a bookie?
- Yeah, she was.

01:06:36.741 --> 01:06:38.658
She single-handedly established...

01:06:38.741 --> 01:06:41.075
this underground gambling ring
at UC Berkeley...

01:06:41.158 --> 01:06:43.867
took bets on every sporting event
imaginable, ran numbers...

01:06:43.951 --> 01:06:46.867
and even hosted a Vegas night
at her sorority house.

01:06:46.951 --> 01:06:49.368
- You're lying.
- No, that was Fran.

01:06:49.451 --> 01:06:52.410
- Orchids? Does that work?
- Yeah, orchids would work.

01:06:52.451 --> 01:06:53.742
Okay.

01:06:53.826 --> 01:06:55.742
Yeah, she was the coolest.

01:06:55.826 --> 01:06:59.035
I was the bookworm, she was
the wild child, and she picked me.

01:07:00.827 --> 01:07:03.285
- Thank you.
- Enjoy.

01:07:04.619 --> 01:07:06.827
- How about cabbage?
- My God.

01:07:08.452 --> 01:07:10.369
- What's the matter?
- Just hide me.

01:07:10.452 --> 01:07:13.412
- Mary, what are you doing?
- Don't say my name!

01:07:13.495 --> 01:07:14.994
Oh, my God.

01:07:34.454 --> 01:07:35.621
You okay?

01:07:35.705 --> 01:07:37.121
I found it.

01:07:40.246 --> 01:07:42.621
Hi. How you doing?
I'm Steve Edison.

01:07:42.663 --> 01:07:45.622
Keith Richmond.
My wife Wendy.

01:07:45.664 --> 01:07:47.831
Nice to meet you, Wendy.

01:07:49.205 --> 01:07:51.580
So, how do you all know each other?

01:07:52.497 --> 01:07:55.664
- It's a long story.
- Oh, let me tell it.

01:07:55.747 --> 01:07:57.664
It's really a funny story.

01:07:57.748 --> 01:07:59.165
See, Keith...

01:07:59.248 --> 01:08:00.915
was my fiance.

01:08:00.999 --> 01:08:04.456
And Wendy was
his high school girlfriend.

01:08:04.498 --> 01:08:07.915
On the night of our rehearsal dinner,
I found them making out.

01:08:10.082 --> 01:08:12.289
In my car.

01:08:13.291 --> 01:08:15.666
I think that covers
all the high points.

01:08:15.708 --> 01:08:17.666
did I leave anything out?

01:08:21.207 --> 01:08:23.125
- You all right?
- Yeah.

01:08:26.375 --> 01:08:27.792
This home?

01:08:30.084 --> 01:08:32.001
You wanna go up?

01:08:43.377 --> 01:08:45.127
All right? You okay?

01:08:45.167 --> 01:08:49.419
Jezebel was the only queen in the Bible
to be eaten by dogs.

01:08:49.502 --> 01:08:52.502
- Did she fall down in the street?
- That's yours.

01:08:54.085 --> 01:08:56.042
Hang on. Hang on.

01:08:59.586 --> 01:09:03.169
- Mr. And Mrs. Wilfred Barber.
- No, it's not that one.

01:09:04.919 --> 01:09:07.336
Nancy Pong.

01:09:13.212 --> 01:09:14.752
Whoisit?

01:09:14.795 --> 01:09:16.837
Nancy Pong? 2C?

01:09:16.920 --> 01:09:19.712
- Yes.
- Nancy, would you buzz us in, please?

01:09:20.462 --> 01:09:22.837
It's Mary Fiore, 7H.

01:09:22.877 --> 01:09:24.754
Who?

01:09:24.837 --> 01:09:26.087
You don't know me.

01:09:27.171 --> 01:09:29.087
We haven't met because...

01:09:30.255 --> 01:09:32.839
I'm a control freak...

01:09:32.879 --> 01:09:35.337
and I don't have time for people.

01:09:37.087 --> 01:09:40.005
But if you ever need
to borrow a cup of sugar...

01:09:41.212 --> 01:09:43.131
I can't help you...

01:09:45.339 --> 01:09:47.798
'cause I don't have time to shop.

01:09:58.215 --> 01:10:00.173
I wanna go home.

01:10:01.465 --> 01:10:03.132
We are home.

01:10:03.215 --> 01:10:05.841
We're just out on the porch.

01:10:05.883 --> 01:10:07.340
All right?

01:10:09.173 --> 01:10:11.091
He's married...

01:10:12.592 --> 01:10:14.884
and they're gonna have a baby.

01:10:17.466 --> 01:10:19.383
And he looked good.

01:10:20.466 --> 01:10:21.758
No, he didn't.

01:10:21.843 --> 01:10:24.302
- No, he really didn't.
- He did.

01:10:27.845 --> 01:10:31.137
Hold it there, please. Thank you.
Here we go. We're in.

01:10:31.178 --> 01:10:34.636
- I don't know him.
- I know, but he'll hold the door for us.

01:10:34.720 --> 01:10:37.803
Come here. Here we go.
Stand up.

01:10:37.887 --> 01:10:39.803
Hold that position. Here we go.

01:10:39.887 --> 01:10:43.346
We got your beer, we got your purse,
we got you, we got your keys.

01:10:43.429 --> 01:10:45.721
Hi there.
Here we go.

01:10:45.762 --> 01:10:48.721
This is somebody that lives
in the same building. Thank you.

01:10:48.762 --> 01:10:50.929
Are you Nancy Pong?

01:10:52.305 --> 01:10:54.430
Okay, a little bit more.

01:10:56.805 --> 01:10:58.722
A little fire.

01:11:05.347 --> 01:11:07.264
Medium well.

01:11:08.555 --> 01:11:11.473
You really don't think
he looked good?

01:11:11.557 --> 01:11:13.973
Oh, no.
He looked old.

01:11:14.056 --> 01:11:15.890
You know?

01:11:15.931 --> 01:11:18.973
Unhappy and fat.
He put on a couple pounds.

01:11:19.056 --> 01:11:20.473
Be quiet.

01:11:26.474 --> 01:11:28.932
He said they were just friends...

01:11:30.308 --> 01:11:32.391
but deep down, I knew better.

01:11:39.683 --> 01:11:41.601
I was just a stand-in.

01:11:43.142 --> 01:11:45.225
A poor man's Wendy.

01:11:49.933 --> 01:11:52.559
She threw my bridal shower for me.

01:11:52.642 --> 01:11:56.893
She even took time to freeze mint leaves
and raspberries in ice cubes.

01:11:56.934 --> 01:12:00.059
That should've tipped me off
right there.

01:12:00.143 --> 01:12:02.059
She was trying too hard.

01:12:06.852 --> 01:12:08.268
Jerk.

01:12:12.269 --> 01:12:15.311
It's a good thing I didn't marry him.

01:12:21.519 --> 01:12:23.936
But most of the time I think...

01:12:28.021 --> 01:12:30.604
I just wasn't enough.

01:12:36.104 --> 01:12:38.520
No, no, no, you're wrong.

01:12:44.772 --> 01:12:46.688
And another thing.

01:12:49.313 --> 01:12:50.730
This Wendy...

01:12:52.855 --> 01:12:56.065
she's nothing but a poor man's Mary.

01:13:25.816 --> 01:13:27.233
It's getting late.

01:13:32.858 --> 01:13:34.608
I'd better go.

01:13:40.026 --> 01:13:41.984
I'll walk you to the door.

01:13:42.026 --> 01:13:44.984
- That's all right. Stay there.
- No, it's okay.

01:13:47.318 --> 01:13:49.734
- Wait.
- Take your time. You all right?

01:13:56.235 --> 01:13:59.152
Thanks for tonight.
I know that I was a mess.

01:13:59.235 --> 01:14:02.444
No, you weren't a mess.

01:14:03.611 --> 01:14:05.069
A little bit.

01:14:07.027 --> 01:14:08.110
Shut up.

01:14:08.194 --> 01:14:10.779
- You gonna be okay?
- Yeah.

01:14:10.861 --> 01:14:14.820
Two aspirin, a lot of water,
sleep, and a beer in the morning.

01:14:14.862 --> 01:14:16.986
That's the cure.

01:14:17.070 --> 01:14:19.236
- Good night, Mary.
- Good night.

01:14:54.365 --> 01:14:56.531
You ever think about
that night in the park?

01:14:56.615 --> 01:14:57.823
What?

01:15:02.448 --> 01:15:04.406
I barely know you.

01:15:05.740 --> 01:15:08.491
I don't know your dad's first name.

01:15:08.574 --> 01:15:13.158
I don't know if you ever wore braces
or contacts or glasses.

01:15:13.241 --> 01:15:16.158
I have no idea how you came to be
a wedding planner, Mary.

01:15:22.075 --> 01:15:24.242
But I know
the curves of your face...

01:15:27.368 --> 01:15:30.326
and I know every feck of gold
in your eyes.

01:15:35.577 --> 01:15:37.869
And I know that
that night in the park...

01:15:41.329 --> 01:15:43.912
was the best time I've ever had.

01:15:58.205 --> 01:15:59.913
Please say something.

01:16:01.955 --> 01:16:04.538
I'm a magnet for unavailable men...

01:16:08.122 --> 01:16:10.081
and I'm sick of it.

01:16:14.581 --> 01:16:15.997
It's simple.

01:16:18.331 --> 01:16:19.789
I know Fran.

01:16:21.498 --> 01:16:22.957
I respect her.

01:16:25.457 --> 01:16:26.915
And she loves you.

01:16:31.666 --> 01:16:34.249
So, besides your tux measurements...

01:16:36.249 --> 01:16:38.208
that's all I need to know.

01:16:45.333 --> 01:16:47.041
Please go away.

01:16:54.292 --> 01:16:56.084
Good night, Mary.

01:17:17.794 --> 01:17:19.752
How do you word an invitation...

01:17:19.794 --> 01:17:22.253
where both sets ofparents
are paying for the wedding...

01:17:22.294 --> 01:17:25.253
the groom is in the military,
about to receive a medical degree...

01:17:25.294 --> 01:17:28.920
and the bride is a widow whose father
recently had a sex-change operation...

01:17:29.003 --> 01:17:32.461
and now goes by the name
Sugar Pie de Santo?

01:17:32.545 --> 01:17:34.503
- Mary?
- What is it?

01:17:34.545 --> 01:17:36.503
A little tense?

01:17:36.545 --> 01:17:39.504
Just terribly, terribly...

01:17:39.587 --> 01:17:40.671
alert.

01:17:45.379 --> 01:17:46.587
What's the matter?

01:17:46.671 --> 01:17:48.712
I came back early.

01:17:50.712 --> 01:17:53.630
Why?
I mean, is everything okay?

01:17:53.713 --> 01:17:55.880
I've discovered something.

01:17:57.547 --> 01:18:00.964
I've been blind.
I didn't want to see it.

01:18:01.839 --> 01:18:04.422
I tried to ignore the signs.

01:18:05.547 --> 01:18:07.631
I think you know
what I'm talking about.

01:18:07.673 --> 01:18:11.382
Let me explain.
It's not what you think.

01:18:11.465 --> 01:18:12.923
Yes, it is.

01:18:14.673 --> 01:18:16.714
I can't go through with this wedding.

01:18:18.465 --> 01:18:20.006
But, Fran...

01:18:20.048 --> 01:18:23.424
I was in a meeting
talking about Boccolino mozzarella...

01:18:23.508 --> 01:18:26.425
and it hit me
that this isn't going to work.

01:18:27.799 --> 01:18:30.924
I can't stand the way
he chews on pen caps...

01:18:31.007 --> 01:18:33.966
or the songs
that he sings in the shower.

01:18:34.007 --> 01:18:39.634
It drives me nuts, how he hikes up his
left pant leg after he's eaten too much.

01:18:41.008 --> 01:18:45.092
Is Eddie gonna be the last man
that I sleep with...

01:18:45.175 --> 01:18:46.592
ever?

01:18:48.551 --> 01:18:53.009
I've been with him so long, I don't
even know why we're together anymore.

01:19:00.926 --> 01:19:02.218
Look at me.

01:19:05.301 --> 01:19:07.219
You are exquisite.

01:19:09.886 --> 01:19:11.052
You're timeless.

01:19:13.219 --> 01:19:16.177
And you have the love
of a man named Steve.

01:19:18.177 --> 01:19:23.637
A man who, while you were away having
meetings about mozzarella, said to me...

01:19:23.721 --> 01:19:26.637
"I can't believe she picked me.

01:19:29.303 --> 01:19:33.262
I can't believe I'm marrying the most
incredible woman I've ever met."

01:19:39.638 --> 01:19:42.596
So that tells me
that this marriage of yours...

01:19:44.013 --> 01:19:45.972
is not only gonna work...

01:19:48.596 --> 01:19:50.723
it's gonna last forever.

01:19:53.305 --> 01:19:54.431
Really?

01:19:57.181 --> 01:19:58.389
Really.

01:20:02.140 --> 01:20:03.597
Thank you.

01:20:07.432 --> 01:20:09.391
Thank you, thank you.

01:20:12.974 --> 01:20:13.099
For he's a jolly good fellow

01:20:13.099 --> 01:20:15.266
For he's a jolly good fellow

01:20:15.349 --> 01:20:18.182
For he's a jolly good fellow

01:20:18.266 --> 01:20:20.808
Which nobody can deny

01:20:22.516 --> 01:20:25.434
Let me pray, let me pray.

01:20:33.808 --> 01:20:36.767
Hope he didn't spit on the cake.

01:20:36.809 --> 01:20:38.892
Come on.
Open up your presents.

01:20:40.560 --> 01:20:44.059
No, no, please.
Everyone, I want to make some toast.

01:20:46.518 --> 01:20:49.270
- Happy birthday, Burt.
- Salute.

01:20:50.937 --> 01:20:53.354
Buddy Burt.
Salvatore.

01:20:53.438 --> 01:20:57.479
I want to thank Salvatore
for taking me into his life...

01:20:57.563 --> 01:21:00.812
and introducing me
to all you wonderful people.

01:21:05.063 --> 01:21:06.980
Hold on a moment.

01:21:08.896 --> 01:21:10.814
Where is he going?

01:21:42.566 --> 01:21:47.190
I know I never done the right thing,
I never say the right thing...

01:21:47.274 --> 01:21:49.357
and I act like a fool.

01:21:52.609 --> 01:21:56.191
I know I say
we're just buddy-buddy friends...

01:21:56.275 --> 01:21:59.233
but that would not be true
to my heart.

01:22:00.901 --> 01:22:03.525
So I would ask you
this one question.

01:22:03.609 --> 01:22:05.526
And if you answer no...

01:22:07.568 --> 01:22:10.526
then I will leave you alone
once and for all.

01:22:15.610 --> 01:22:18.152
Be my wife, Mary Fiore...

01:22:19.903 --> 01:22:25.320
and I will take care of you
and be true to you...

01:22:25.361 --> 01:22:29.028
and, like this house
I built for your dolls...

01:22:29.111 --> 01:22:33.236
I will make sure you have
a strong roof over your head.

01:22:33.320 --> 01:22:36.196
If your answer is yes...

01:22:36.237 --> 01:22:39.820
then no one will ever love you
as much as I love you.

01:22:41.570 --> 01:22:43.528
If your answer is yes...

01:22:45.487 --> 01:22:48.945
you will make me
the happiest man on the Earth.

01:25:36.667 --> 01:25:38.626
What would I have done
without you?

01:25:38.667 --> 01:25:41.459
Hey, wedding woman,
you did some job.

01:25:41.542 --> 01:25:44.833
My girl's gonna knock 'em dead.
Aren't you, sluggo?

01:25:44.917 --> 01:25:48.834
Well, somebody stole my lucky mike.
I can't sing without my lucky mike.

01:26:27.714 --> 01:26:29.297
What are you doing here?

01:26:29.381 --> 01:26:32.507
You know it's bad luck
to see the bride before the wedding.

01:26:35.757 --> 01:26:37.007
You look beautiful.

01:26:37.840 --> 01:26:41.423
Go on. Get out of here.
We're starting any minute.

01:26:41.507 --> 01:26:42.924
Come on.

01:26:44.298 --> 01:26:47.383
- Let's take a walk.
- A walk?

01:26:47.466 --> 01:26:49.841
A walk. Come on.

01:26:49.925 --> 01:26:51.341
Come on.

01:26:53.591 --> 01:26:56.175
No. What are you talking about?
You cannot give the whole wedding to me.

01:26:56.258 --> 01:26:59.050
Everything is gonna be fine.
It's a no-brainer.

01:26:59.133 --> 01:27:01.008
You can't do this.
Geri's out there!

01:27:01.050 --> 01:27:04.051
So?
The whole commission is yours.

01:27:05.759 --> 01:27:07.343
That's more money
than I make in a year.

01:27:07.425 --> 01:27:11.301
Then I guess that means we're gonna
have to go shopping next week.

01:27:13.259 --> 01:27:16.259
I am completely confused.
Why are you doing this?

01:27:17.802 --> 01:27:18.885
Because there's somewhere
I've gotta be.

01:27:19.969 --> 01:27:22.843
Okay, we can talk
afterthe wedding.

01:27:22.927 --> 01:27:24.927
Hang on a minute, Fran.

01:27:27.344 --> 01:27:31.428
- Why do you wanna marry me?
- What?

01:27:31.512 --> 01:27:33.678
That's one of the questions
I need answered.

01:27:35.220 --> 01:27:36.886
Steve, you're scaring me.

01:27:38.053 --> 01:27:39.512
You never call me Steve.

01:27:40.262 --> 01:27:41.761
That's because you don't like it.

01:27:44.136 --> 01:27:46.096
I never said I didn't like it.

01:27:48.638 --> 01:27:51.680
- Okay, where is this going?
- Why do you wanna marry me?

01:27:53.971 --> 01:27:55.971
Are you kidding me?

01:27:56.012 --> 01:27:57.971
- Are you kidding me?
- No, I'm not.

01:27:58.012 --> 01:28:01.639
You're trying to dump me
on the day of my wedding.

01:28:01.681 --> 01:28:04.930
- I just need to know your answer.
- This is not happening to me.

01:28:05.013 --> 01:28:07.514
- Franny, Franny.
- This is... don't "Franny" me!

01:28:07.597 --> 01:28:10.180
don't "Franny" me,
you selfish bastard!

01:28:10.264 --> 01:28:13.055
The reasons we were together in college
don't hold up anymore.

01:28:13.138 --> 01:28:15.097
We're different people now.

01:28:15.138 --> 01:28:17.682
- And?
- And I think you know that.

01:28:19.014 --> 01:28:20.931
Listen to me.

01:28:21.014 --> 01:28:24.014
If you really love me,
I'll put this cummerbund on right now...

01:28:24.098 --> 01:28:27.473
we'll walk up that hill
and go to the big tent and do it.

01:28:27.515 --> 01:28:30.223
- You would do that?
- Yes, I would.

01:28:32.849 --> 01:28:34.683
All those people.

01:28:34.766 --> 01:28:37.307
You don't know half of'em.

01:28:38.891 --> 01:28:40.808
You and me.

01:28:42.558 --> 01:28:43.975
Are you ready?

01:28:47.225 --> 01:28:50.141
Yes. Yes, of course.

01:28:53.600 --> 01:28:55.809
I just need a second.

01:29:03.560 --> 01:29:04.977
Oh, God.

01:29:27.270 --> 01:29:30.187
I don't want to get married.

01:30:21.982 --> 01:30:24.898
How did we let it get this far?

01:30:26.399 --> 01:30:27.898
I don't know.

01:30:29.149 --> 01:30:31.233
What are we gonna do?

01:30:33.233 --> 01:30:36.233
Well, that's the beauty of it.

01:30:36.316 --> 01:30:38.275
Whatever we want.

01:30:41.442 --> 01:30:45.609
I haven't thought about
what I really want in so long.

01:30:45.693 --> 01:30:47.109
Me neither.

01:30:55.860 --> 01:30:58.359
There you go.

01:31:04.069 --> 01:31:05.152
Okay.

01:31:06.777 --> 01:31:08.944
Okay.

01:31:19.697 --> 01:31:22.947
That is the bride.
Is that the bride?

01:31:23.030 --> 01:31:24.822
Yes, it is.

01:31:24.864 --> 01:31:27.280
Well, is she coming back?

01:31:31.157 --> 01:31:34.906
I think all the blood is rushing
to my head and I'm gonna faint.

01:31:34.948 --> 01:31:37.448
I'm gonna kill Mary
for leaving me all alone here.

01:31:37.489 --> 01:31:39.489
- I don't know what to do.
- Penny, take a breath.

01:31:39.573 --> 01:31:41.656
What are you talking about?

01:31:41.740 --> 01:31:44.824
I'm talking about your wedding planner
leaving me here all alone...

01:31:44.907 --> 01:31:47.074
to go to city hall
and get married.

01:31:47.158 --> 01:31:49.074
Married?

01:31:49.158 --> 01:31:51.824
- What? Mary's getting married?
- Yeah, married.

01:31:51.907 --> 01:31:54.366
- You know, married?
- No, she can't get married.

01:31:54.408 --> 01:31:56.366
- Married.
- Hey, hey, city hall.

01:31:56.408 --> 01:31:59.867
Married, you know, like what
you're supposed to be doing.

01:31:59.908 --> 01:32:02.658
Oh, that's... Yeah.

01:32:02.742 --> 01:32:07.034
That's great. Go. I'll tell everyone.
I'll tell Kathie Lee Gifford.

01:32:12.992 --> 01:32:15.201
Beautiful.

01:32:15.285 --> 01:32:16.826
Thanks.

01:32:50.620 --> 01:32:52.746
Come on! Goddamn it.

01:32:52.829 --> 01:32:55.245
Are you sure you
don't know a shortcut?

01:32:55.329 --> 01:32:57.579
Take a shortcut somewhere?

01:32:57.662 --> 01:32:59.580
- What do you expect me...
- Bullshit.

01:32:59.663 --> 01:33:01.872
What are you doing?

01:33:03.663 --> 01:33:06.371
Hold on the right. Hold!

01:33:16.623 --> 01:33:19.873
We are gathered together
in the presence of these witnesses...

01:33:19.956 --> 01:33:23.372
tojoin this man and this woman...

01:33:23.456 --> 01:33:25.456
in matrimony.

01:33:25.497 --> 01:33:28.290
This contract is not
to be taken lightly...

01:33:28.332 --> 01:33:32.082
but thought fully and seriously...

01:33:32.165 --> 01:33:34.540
with a deep realization...

01:33:34.582 --> 01:33:39.082
of its obligations
and responsibilities.

01:33:39.166 --> 01:33:41.124
If anyone can show just cause...

01:33:41.206 --> 01:33:45.374
why these two should not
be joined together in matrimony...

01:33:45.416 --> 01:33:47.958
then let him speak now
or forever...

01:33:48.042 --> 01:33:49.958
hold his peace.

01:33:55.333 --> 01:33:57.459
Fine.

01:33:57.542 --> 01:34:00.168
- Then let us proceed.
- No.

01:34:01.168 --> 01:34:03.792
- Thank God.
- Oh, hell, I object too.

01:34:03.834 --> 01:34:05.168
What is going on here?

01:34:07.542 --> 01:34:08.626
Here we go.

01:34:13.002 --> 01:34:16.919
Maria, I look in your eyes
and it hurts my insides.

01:34:17.002 --> 01:34:20.835
This is not what you want.
This is what I want.

01:34:20.919 --> 01:34:22.585
Shame on me.

01:34:22.627 --> 01:34:24.668
I'm so lucky
to have a father like you.

01:34:26.668 --> 01:34:27.961
But you're right.

01:34:29.420 --> 01:34:32.003
Love isn't like
some enchanted evening...

01:34:33.337 --> 01:34:34.961
isn't a fairy tale...

01:34:35.003 --> 01:34:37.503
or even love at first sight.

01:34:38.836 --> 01:34:41.170
That isn't real life.

01:34:44.213 --> 01:34:46.213
Massimo's a good man.

01:34:46.254 --> 01:34:48.046
don't worry, Papa.

01:34:48.129 --> 01:34:50.879
I know what I'm doing.

01:34:52.754 --> 01:34:54.795
I'm just all grown up now.

01:35:01.380 --> 01:35:03.339
Okay.

01:35:08.672 --> 01:35:10.464
Hey, that's the doc!

01:35:10.506 --> 01:35:12.798
- Steve!
- Oh, yes.

01:35:12.881 --> 01:35:15.048
- You know the doctor?
- Mary. Where's Mary?

01:35:15.131 --> 01:35:17.048
I'm her father.
Who the hell are you?

01:35:17.131 --> 01:35:19.298
- He's the doctor.
- I'm Steve, the doctor.

01:35:19.381 --> 01:35:21.798
- I'm in love with your daughter.
- You are the one?

01:35:21.882 --> 01:35:24.632
- What the hell is going on?
- I'm sorry, but I am.

01:35:24.715 --> 01:35:27.341
- What about Fran?
- Fran and I did not get married.

01:35:27.424 --> 01:35:29.341
That's been happening a lot today.

01:35:29.424 --> 01:35:31.090
Whoa. You didn't get married?

01:35:31.132 --> 01:35:34.716
We're not married. I am not the one.
You are the one, Steve.

01:35:34.799 --> 01:35:37.132
And you didn't get married?
She's not married?

01:35:37.216 --> 01:35:40.758
She does not love me.
She loves you, Steve.

01:35:42.342 --> 01:35:46.509
I could never forgive myself ifever
I got in the way of Mary's true love.

01:35:46.550 --> 01:35:48.884
- Who the hell are you?
- I'm Steve.

01:35:48.967 --> 01:35:50.300
He's Steve. He's the one.

01:35:50.383 --> 01:35:52.342
I'm the doctor.
I'm in love with Mary.

01:35:52.383 --> 01:35:54.342
Wait a minute!
Hold the phone.

01:35:54.425 --> 01:35:58.093
You mean to tell me,
you love her and she loves you...

01:35:58.176 --> 01:36:00.177
and neither of you
got married today?

01:36:00.259 --> 01:36:01.927
That's what I'm saying.

01:36:01.968 --> 01:36:05.010
Then what the hell are you
standing around talking to us for?

01:36:05.093 --> 01:36:08.301
I don't know. Where is she?
Where is Mary? Somebody take me to Mary.

01:36:08.343 --> 01:36:09.843
I take you. Come on.

01:36:09.927 --> 01:36:12.094
- I like him.
- He's a doctor.

01:36:22.761 --> 01:36:24.803
Congratulations!

01:36:24.886 --> 01:36:26.223
Fabulous!

01:36:26.306 --> 01:36:28.264
Good for you!

01:36:30.098 --> 01:36:33.430
- Congratulations!
- Go, go. Thank you.

01:36:56.183 --> 01:36:58.100
Thank you, Massimo!

01:36:58.183 --> 01:37:00.308
You better be good to her!

01:37:00.391 --> 01:37:03.183
I still do more chin-ups than you!

01:37:31.102 --> 01:37:34.060
Why are you only eating
the brown ones?

01:37:43.228 --> 01:37:46.144
Because someone once said that...

01:37:46.228 --> 01:37:50.186
they had less artificial coloring
because chocolate's already brown.

01:37:55.646 --> 01:37:57.729
And it kind of stayed with me.

01:38:03.729 --> 01:38:05.562
You kind of stayed with me.

01:38:14.980 --> 01:38:16.438
Where's Fran?

01:38:17.480 --> 01:38:20.230
She's in Tahiti...

01:38:20.313 --> 01:38:22.230
on our honeymoon.

01:38:25.148 --> 01:38:26.773
We didn't get married.

01:38:31.606 --> 01:38:32.690
Because?

01:38:35.232 --> 01:38:38.481
Because she needs to
find her own life.

01:38:44.358 --> 01:38:46.233
And I...

01:38:48.983 --> 01:38:50.400
You what?

01:38:53.649 --> 01:38:55.234
What does Steve want?

01:38:56.359 --> 01:38:57.984
I want to dance...

01:39:01.984 --> 01:39:03.858
with you.

